{% comment %}
  Care Instructions Page
  Guide for caring for products
{% endcomment %}

<div class="pt-32 pb-24 min-h-screen bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    
    {%- comment -%} Breadcrumb {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8 flex items-center gap-2">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-black transition-colors">Home</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span class="text-black font-medium">Care Instructions</span>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="font-serif-display text-5xl text-gray-900 mb-4">
        Care Instructions
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">
        Learn how to properly care for your Sgroi Fashion pieces to keep them looking beautiful.
      </p>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%} Care Guide Sections {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="space-y-12">
      
      {%- comment -%} Section 1: General Care {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-6 py-4">
        <h2 class="font-serif-display text-3xl text-gray-900 mb-4">General Care</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-gray-600 space-y-3">
          <p>All of our pieces are designed to be durable and long-lasting. Follow these basic guidelines to maintain the quality of your items:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 list-inside">
            <li>• Always check the garment care label for specific instructions</li>
            <li>• Sort laundry by color - separate whites, lights, and darks</li>
            <li>• Use cold water for colored garments to prevent fading</li>
            <li>• Turn garments inside out before washing to minimize pilling</li>
            <li>• Use gentle detergent - avoid bleach or harsh chemicals</li>
            <li>• Machine wash on delicate cycle or hand wash when possible</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%} Section 2: Drying {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-6 py-4">
        <h2 class="font-serif-display text-3xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Drying</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-gray-600 space-y-3">
          <p>Proper drying techniques help preserve the shape and longevity of your pieces:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 list-inside">
            <li>• Air dry flat or on a hanger whenever possible</li>
            <li>• Avoid using high heat in the dryer - use low or no heat setting</li>
            <li>• Remove from dryer immediately to prevent wrinkles</li>
            <li>• Don't hang heavy, wet items as they may stretch</li>
            <li>• Dry delicate pieces flat on a clean towel</li>
            <li>• Keep away from direct sunlight to prevent fading</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%} Section 3: Storage {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-6 py-4">
        <h2 class="font-serif-display text-3xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Storage</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-gray-600 space-y-3">
          <p>Store your pieces properly to maintain their condition:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 list-inside">
            <li>• Fold or hang items in a clean, dry place</li>
            <li>• Use hangers for dresses and delicate pieces</li>
            <li>• Fold heavier knits to prevent stretching</li>
            <li>• Store in breathable garment bags or containers</li>
            <li>• Keep away from moisture and extreme temperatures</li>
            <li>• Use cedar blocks or lavender sachets to prevent moths</li>
            <li>• Remove from plastic bags immediately after purchase</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%} Section 4: Stain Removal {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-6 py-4">
        <h2 class="font-serif-display text-3xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Stain Removal</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-gray-600 space-y-3">
          <p>Act quickly for best results when treating stains:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 list-inside">
            <li>• Blot stains with a clean white cloth - don't rub</li>
            <li>• Work from the outside of the stain toward the center</li>
            <li>• Treat stains promptly before washing</li>
            <li>• Test any stain remover on a hidden area first</li>
            <li>• Use cold water for protein-based stains (blood, egg)</li>
            <li>• Use warm water for oil-based stains</li>
            <li>• For stubborn stains, consider professional dry cleaning</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%} Section 5: Ironing & Pressing {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-6 py-4">
        <h2 class="font-serif-display text-3xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Ironing & Pressing</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-gray-600 space-y-3">
          <p>Keep your pieces looking crisp and polished:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 list-inside">
            <li>• Check the care label for heat recommendations</li>
            <li>• Use low to medium heat for delicate fabrics</li>
            <li>• Always iron on the reverse side when possible</li>
            <li>• Use a pressing cloth for silk and delicate materials</li>
            <li>• Iron seams and hems last</li>
            <li>• Don't iron over buttons or embellishments</li>
            <li>• Hang immediately after pressing to avoid new wrinkles</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%} Section 6: Material-Specific Care {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-6 py-4">
        <h2 class="font-serif-display text-3xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Material-Specific Care</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          {%- comment -%} Cotton {%- endcomment -%}
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Cotton</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Hardy and easy to care for. Machine wash warm, dry on medium heat. Cotton shrinks slightly when new, so we pre-shrink our pieces.</p>
          </div>

          {%- comment -%} Silk {%- endcomment -%}
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Silk</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Delicate and luxurious. Hand wash or use delicate cycle in cold water. Avoid wringing. Lay flat to dry. Iron on low heat with steam.</p>
          </div>

          {%- comment -%} Polyester {%- endcomment -%}
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Polyester</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Durable and wrinkle-resistant. Machine wash in warm water, tumble dry on low. Avoid high heat to prevent damage.</p>
          </div>

          {%- comment -%} Linen {%- endcomment -%}
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Linen</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Breathable and comfortable. Hand wash or machine wash on gentle cycle. Linen wrinkles easily - this is natural. Iron on medium to high heat.</p>
          </div>

          {%- comment -%} Wool {%- endcomment -%}
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Wool</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Warm and durable. Hand wash in cold water with gentle detergent. Lay flat to dry. Avoid heat and strong agitation to prevent felting.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    {%- comment -%} CTA Section {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="mt-16 bg-pink-50 p-8 rounded-lg border border-pink-200">
      <h3 class="font-serif-display text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Still have questions?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Our customer service team is here to help with any specific care questions about your pieces.</p>
      <a href="/pages/contact" class="inline-block px-8 py-3 bg-black text-white rounded-full font-bold hover:bg-pink-500 transition-colors">
        Contact Us
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

